1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper primarily focuses on device-to-device communication in cellular networks, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses resource allocation and throughput maximization, which are key topics in information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the use of millimeter wave communication, which is a key technology in multimedia communication. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an architecture for optimal resource allocation, which involves system design and control. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper briefly mentions security issues associated with D2D communication, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security.
